<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6b2a7a7c-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s426g–1"><num value="426g–1">§ 426g–1.</num><heading> State and regional plans</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id6b2a7a7d-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s426g–1/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> cooperate with any State in the preparation of a comprehensive State or regional plan for the conservation of coastal resources located within the boundaries of the State;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id6b2a7a7e-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s426g–1/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> encourage State participation in the implementation of the plan; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id6b2a7a7f-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s426g–1/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> submit to Congress reports and recommendations with respect to appropriate Federal participation in carrying out the plan.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id6b2a7a80-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/act/1946-08-13/ch960/s4">Aug. 13, 1946, ch. 960, § 4</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/104/303/tII/s227/d/2">Pub. L. 104–303, title II, § 227(d)(2)</ref>, <date date="1996-10-12">Oct. 12, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/3700">110 Stat. 3700</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6b2a7a81-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id6b2a7a82-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="id6b2a7a83-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">A prior section 4 of act <date date="1946-08-13">Aug. 13, 1946</date>, was renumbered section 5 of that act, and was classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t33/s426h">section 426h of this title</ref> prior to repeal by <ref href="/us/pl/104/303">Pub. L. 104–303</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
